name: AHMAD ZAYED
bio: [('Beginning', 'He took up the sport at age 15. (qatar-tribune.com, 07 Jun 2017)'), ('Reason', 'He used to be a football player but decided to quit because his training interfered with his studies. "For the next three years, I was fully focused on my academics until one day when my school participated in the School Olympic Program [SOP] and we were taken to the Lusail Shooting Range. I volunteered to be a part of my school team. I liked what I saw there and I performed well." One of the coaches at Lusail noticed him and decided to mentor him in the sport. (qatar-tribune.com, 07 Jun 2017)'), ('Debut', '2014 in Doha, Qatar (qatar-tribune.com, 07 Jun 2017)'), ('Additional Information', 'GeneralFOCUSED ON STUDIESDue to the fact that he will finish his studies by the time the 2020 Olympic Games in Tokyo start, he might not be able to qualify given the importance of training and preparations before the Games. "I\'ll need a minimum of one-year dedicated training both within and outside Qatar before I can be fully ready for the Games and I don\'t think that will be possible. So the sport requires time and my academics is the main priority for now." (qatar-tribune.com, 07 Jun 2017) '), ('Hero', 'Turkish shooter Yusuf Dikec. name: ABDULLA
bio: [('Beginning', 'He began playing squash at age six, and turned professional in 2011. (thepeninsulaqatar.com, 16 Jun 2014; squashinfo.com, 01 Apr 2018)'), ('Reason', '"I started squash as a hobby. I also used to play football and it used to be my life.
